# Documentation Required

- Any product, UX, behavior, test-data, or implementation change in this project must also update the relevant project documentation.
- Planning specs, exports, and parity notes live under **`Planning/`** at the repo root; keep them aligned when product or verification behavior changes.
- At minimum, review and update the applicable planning docs and test-scenario docs (including root-level `FEATURE_TEST_SCENARIOS.md`, `PRODUCTION_READINESS_CHECKLIST.md`, and `RUN_MVP_LOCALLY_AND_ON_PHONE.md` when relevant).
- If a new feature or rule is added, document it in the same task by default unless the user explicitly says not to.

## Minute-precision log (mandatory on code changes)

- See **`timestamped-changelog.mdc`**: every `(code)` edit appends **`Planning/DATED_CHANGE_LOG.md`** with a to-the-minute timestamp and brief description.
- **`Planning/CHANGELOG.md`** remains the human-facing release notes (topic buckets); it does not replace the dated log.

## Cursor workflow (this repo)

| Step | Rule file |
|------|-----------|
| User must start message with `(code)` to allow edits | `code-permission-gate.mdc` |
| After edits, ask if user wants a git commit | `commit-prompt-after-code.mdc` |
| Append DATED_CHANGE_LOG entry per change batch | `timestamped-changelog.mdc` |
